#Text=Ontario Votes 2007 : Interview with Green Party candidate Brett McKenzie , London North Centre
#Text=Saturday , October 6 , 2007
#Text=is running for the Green Party of Ontario in the Ontario provincial election , in the London North Centre riding .
#Text=Wikinews ' Nick Moreau interviewed him regarding his values , his experience , and his campaign .
#Text=Stay tuned for further interviews ; every candidate from every party is eligible , and will be contacted .

#Text=Expect interviews from Liberals , Progressive Conservatives , New Democratic Party members , Ontario Greens , as well as members from the Family Coalition , Freedom , Communist , Libertarian , and Confederation of Regions parties , as well as independents .
#Text=Interview
#Text=Why have you chosen to involve yourself in the political process ?
#Text=Why did you choose to run in this constituency ?
#Text=The first time I was able to vote , in the fall of the year I turned eighteen , I read the platforms and policies of the various parties and I voted Green .
#Text=After that , I started voting against people .
#Text=For ten years , I inflicted my vote on the politician I thought was the worst , rather than awarding it to the best .
#Text=I felt disenfranchised .
#Text=I really had no voice in this democracy , except to complain .
#Text=Finally , I had had enough , and voted the way I really wanted to .
#Text=After that , I was happy about democracy again .
#Text=I 've been hooked ever since .
#Text=This is where the future is decided .
#Text=The exchange of ideas is vital to the process , and it 's my favourite part .
#Text=Some of the highlights of this campaign have been conversations with competing parties .
#Text=I 'm running in London North Centre because it 's where I live , and I want to be able to shape the destiny of my neighbourhood , in my city , in my province .
#Text=What prior political experience do you have ?
#Text=What skills and insight can you bring to office , from other non-political positions you may have held ?
#Text=I 've been a member of the Green Party since 2004 , shortly after the last election .
#Text=I 've been on the Constituency Association since shortly after I joined .
#Text=This is my first run for public office .
#Text=I have been involved politically with the Kinsmen and Kinettes of Canada : club executive , club president , district treasurer and secretary , and in a bid for national office , as well .
#Text=I understand democracy , the history of Ontario , the issues at hand , and the steps required to address those issues .
#Text=I understand other cultures and all faiths .
#Text=I understand people from all backgrounds .
#Text=I am intelligent .
#Text=I am a problem-solver .
#Text=Which of your competitors do you expect to pose the biggest challenge to your candidacy ?
#Text=Why ?
#Text=What makes you the most desirable of all candidates running in the riding ?
#Text=The incumbent is the biggest challenge , aside from the voters themselves .
#Text=The incumbent has the immediate benefit of name recognition and a pretty good track record in office .
#Text=She 's done a pretty good job , just for the wrong party , in my opinion .
#Text=The voters are a challenge because some of the policies that the Green Party are suggesting seem strange and radical .
#Text=In some ways , they are : comprehensive , inclusive , and holistic .
#Text=We do n't compartmentalize policy .
#Text=Transit=climate change=health=economy .
#Text=They 're all connected .
#Text=And that 's what makes any Green candidate the best option :
#Text=we 're thinking of the whole picture , now and tomorrow .
#Text=I understand this city .
#Text=I understand this province .
#Text=I understand the challenges we will face , and I 'm prepared to take step NOW to address them .
#Text=I 'm ready to educate the other politicians in Queen 's Park , and tell them what I think needs to be done .
#Text=I also know that there 's no such thing as a free lunch , and we 're going to have to pay up , sooner or later .
#Text=i do n't want my daughter to have to pick up the tab .
